Useful Reference
https://webdriver.io/docs/gettingstarted.html
http://v4.webdriver.io/guide/getstarted/install.html


Install brew
Install Node with brew
Use Visual Studio Code as IDE (optional recommendation)
Or Install WebdriverIO via terminal (Install in the same folder as the Test Code)

- Create a package json  (similar to maven or nugget)
-- npm init -y
- Install WebdriverIO CLI
-- npm i --save-dev @wdio/cli
- Generate configuration file
-- ./node_modules/.bin/wdio config
-- answer questions
- Create spec files
-- mkdir -p ./test/specs
-- touch ./test/specs/basic.js
- Kick off Testrunner
-- ./node_modules/.bin/wdio wdio.conf.js
